OL,3,CKing's official birthday to be
OL,4,Ccelebrated with Trooping the Colour
OL,6,FCrowds will be treated to the sight of
OL,7,Fa royal carriage procession along The
OL,8,FMall as the King, Queen and the
OL,9,FPrincess of Wales, likely to be joined
OL,10,Fby her children, are guarded by a
OL,11,FSovereign's Escort provided by the
OL,12,FHousehold Cavalry Mounted Regiment.
OL,14,FRiding in the formation will be the
OL,15,Froyal colonels ` the Prince of Wales,
OL,16,Fwho is Colonel of the Welsh Guards;
OL,17,Fthe Princess Royal, Colonel of the
OL,18,FBlues and Royals; and the Duke of
OL,19,FEdinburgh as Colonel of the Scots
OL,20,FGuards.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
