OL,3,CKing's official birthday to be
OL,4,Ccelebrated with Trooping the Colour
OL,6,FThe Grenadier Guards were raised in
OL,7,F1656 in Bruges, Belgium, by the exiled
OL,8,FKing Charles II to protect him during
OL,9,Fthe period Olive Cromwell ruled
OL,10,FEngland.
OL,12,FCharles, Colonel-in-Chief of the
OL,13,FGrenadier Guards, visited his King's
OL,14,FCompany at their barracks in Aldershot
OL,15,Fon the eve of Trooping and wished them
OL,16,F"great success" for the big day.
